File: internal/client/providers/grpc/tlsconfig.go
Package: grpc
Role: Security Factory Configuration
Purpose: Generates tailored x509 cryptographic contexts isolating client connection privileges across explicit lifecycle steps (bootstrap vs mTLS).

Functions:
func ConfigForBootstrap() (*tls.Config, error). Purpose: unauthenticated state. Loads ServerCAPool as target RootCAs anchor without local identities. Errors: wrapped CA mapping failures.
func ConfigForMTLS(cert tls.Certificate, caPool *x509.CertPool) (*tls.Config, error). Purpose: authenticated context. Embeds operational device identity certificate inside safe TLS handshake frameworks. Errors: wrapped CA fallback pool failures.
func ConfigForTest() *tls.Config. Diagnostic stub bypassing certificate identity logic. Enforces InsecureSkipVerify=true.
